#: materiel-component.rst:63
msgid "Entering ``component`` defines the claim and defines the relevant fields to be used in further data entry about a :ref:`component`. For quality assurance purposes, entering ``component`` should create an error if there is any entry for fields tied to other claim types, such as :ref:`materiel` or :ref:`equipment`."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:66
msgid "status:meta"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:72
msgid "A field that classifies the data in the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:87
msgid "``:claim/statuses``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:92
msgid "``accepted``, ``conflict``, ``work_needed``, ``issue``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:97
msgid "Claims are marked ``accepted`` when all of the data can be entered in accordance with the guidance of this handbook. The ``conflict`` flag is used whenever a claim conflicts with another claim (or claims) and a review of citations show it to be the incorrect or false claim (see :ref:`Citations with both Accepted and Conflicted Information` for guidance when one claim from a citation contains both ``accepted`` and ``conflict`` information). A :ref:`public_notes:meta <component-public-notes>` should always accompany any ``conflict`` claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:99
msgid "If the data itself cannot be brought into the SFM standard the flag ``issue`` should be used. Finally, if the current citations cannot establish whether a claim should be flagged as ``accepted`` or ``conflict`` then the flag ``work_needed`` should be used as additional research is needed."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:102
msgid "researcher:meta"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:108
msgid "Field for initials or other identifier of researcher who last entered data for the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:123
msgid "``:meta/researchers``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:128
msgid "``TW``, ``Jane_Doe``, ``G1``"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:133
msgid "Every researcher should use this field to mark the claims that they have entered. Anytime a researcher modifies any data for an existing claim they should update this field so that any questions can be directed to the right person and the flow of work can be better tracked."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:136
msgid "internal_comments:meta"
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:142
msgid "A field for temporary comments or notes for the researcher or research team working on the claim."
msgstr ""

#: materiel-component.rst:152 materiel-component.rst:255 materiel-component.rst:323 materiel-component.rst:425 materiel-component.rst:459 materiel-component.rst:493 materiel-component.rst:527 materiel-component.rst:561 materiel-component.rst:595 materiel-component.rst:629 materiel-component.rst:663 materiel-component.rst:697 materiel-component.rst:733
